briefdescription.para: Helper enum to be used as return value of bt_sdp_discover_func_t. The value informs the caller to perform further pending actions or stop them.
Protocols to be asked about specific parameters.
Callback type reporting to user that there is a resolved result on remote for given UUID and the result record buffer can be used by user for further inspection.

detaileddescription.para: A function of this type is given by the user to the bt_sdp_discover_params object. It'll be called on each valid record discovery completion for given UUID. When UUID resolution gives back no records then NULL is passed to the user. Otherwise user can get valid record(s) and then the internal hint 'next record' is set to false saying the UUID resolution is complete or the hint can be set by caller to true meaning that next record is available for given UUID. The returned function value allows the user to control retrieving follow-up resolved records if any. If the user doesn't want to read more resolved records for given UUID since current record data fulfills its requirements then should return BT_SDP_DISCOVER_UUID_STOP. Otherwise returned value means more subcall iterations are allowable.

parameterdescription.para: Connection object identifying connection to queried remote.
Object pointing to logical unparsed SDP record collected on base of response driven by given UUID.

simplesect.para: BT_SDP_DISCOVER_UUID_STOP in case of no more need to read next record data and continue discovery for given UUID. By returning BT_SDP_DISCOVER_UUID_CONTINUE user allows this discovery continuation.

simplesect.para: 0 in case of success or negative value in case of error.

briefdescription.para: Allows user to start SDP discovery session.

detaileddescription.para: The function performs SDP service discovery on remote server driven by user delivered discovery parameters. Discovery session is made as soon as no SDP transaction is ongoing between peers and if any then this one is queued to be processed at discovery completion of previous one. On the service discovery completion the callback function will be called to get feedback to user about findings.

parameterdescription.para: Object identifying connection to remote.
SDP discovery parameters.

simplesect.para: 0 in case of success or negative value in case of error.

detaileddescription.para: API extracts specific parameter associated with given protocol UUID available in Additional Protocol Descriptor List attribute.

parameterdescription.para: Original buffered raw record data.
Known protocol to be checked like RFCOMM or L2CAP.

There may be more than one parameter realted to the given protocol UUID. This function returns the result that is indexed by this parameter. It's value is from 0, 0 means the first matched result, 1 means the second matched result.
On success populated by found parameter value.
